.TH hsh 27 "April 2023" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
hsh \- a simple shell program
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple shell program that allows users to run commands in the terminal. It can execute programs, display the contents of environment variables, and exit gracefully. It reads commands from standard input until an exit command is entered.

.B hsh
supports the following commands:

.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.

.TP
.B env
Display the current environment variables.

.TP
.B any_command
Execute a command specified by the user. If the command is not found in the system's PATH, an error message is displayed.

.SH RETURN VALUE
.B hsh
returns 0 on successful execution.

.SH EXAMPLES
To run the shell, simply execute the program:

.nf
$ ./hsh
$

To execute a command, enter the command at the prompt:

.nf
$ echo "Hello, World!"
Hello, World!
$

